    "A rough result is created in the rough module, and then pass the key time points in the video clip (the green point in the figure) into the fine module for processing so as to find the precise time position.",
    "\"D Conv Head\" means cascading NL-3D (\"NL\" denotes a non-local block (Wang et al. 2018)).",
    "The 2D Conv head block represents a cascading 2D spatial convolution.",
    "CFAD can achieve this 3.3 times faster than its nearest competitor.",
    "The mainstream one-stage methods still rely on anchoring to generate candidate proposals; they lack generalization ability and cannot fully reflect the performance in complex, changeable action videos."
